    "recap_headline": "University of Oklahoma Athletics",
    "recap_text": "NORMAN\n\u2014 No. 9 Oklahoma erased a four-run deficit to come back and beat No. 22 Texas A&M, 8-7, Friday night in the SEC opener.\nAfter the Aggies (15-2, 0-1) put up four runs at the top of the first, the Sooners (16-2, 1-0) clawed their way back, capped by a go-ahead sacrifice fly from\nDasan Harris\nin the bottom of the eighth.\nOU was powered by six extra-base hits on the night, including back-to-back home runs from\nBrendan Brock\nand\nJaxon Willits\nto tie the game in the sixth.\nTexas A&M put up five runs (three earned) on OU starting left-handed pitcher\nCameron Johnson\n, who allowed just one hit but walked seven to go with two strikeouts in 2.1 innings. The Oklahoma bullpen allowed just two runs the rest of the way on five hits.\nFreshman\nXander Mercurius\nwas the first Sooner out of the pen and fanned a season-high four batters in 1.2 scoreless innings. Lefty\nGavyn Jones\nsurrendered a pair of runs on two hits with two K's and a walk before giving way to\nKadyn Leon\n(0.2 IP) who struck out one with one hit and one walk.\nVeteran junior\nJason Bodin\nearned his second win of the season in relief, hurling the final 2.1 innings and striking out four with no hits allowed and one walk.\nPitchers of Record\nWin:\nJason Bodin\n(2-0)\nLoss: Clayton Freshcorn (2-1)\nStatistical Snapshot\nJaxon Willits\n| 3-for-3, 1 HR, 3 RBI\nBrendan Brock\n| 2-for-3, 1 HR, 1 3B, 3 RBI\nDeiten Lachance\n| 2-for-5, 1 3B, 1 RBI\nXander Mercurius\n| 1.2 IP, 2 H, 0 R, 0 ER, 1 BB, 4 K\nJason Bodin\n| 2.1 IP, 0 H, 0 R, 0 ER, 1 BB, 4 K\nNotes\nOU improved to 16-2 on the season and 12-2 at Kimrey Family Stadium.\nThe Sooners are 1-0 in SEC play with the win. It marks the second straight season OU has opened conference play with a win.\nIt was OU's third straight win over Texas A&M after a pair of wins at the 2022 CWS. The matchup was the first among the teams in Norman since 2011 when the schools were Big 12 foes.\nOU is 2-0 in ranked matchups on the season.\nOU continued its streak of an extra-base hit in every game of the season with six on the day.\nThe Sooner pitching staff struck out 13 batters on the night, the 12th game of 18 this season that the staff has struck out 10-plus.\nOU hit two triples in the first inning courtesy of\nBrendan Brock\nand\nDeiten Lachance\n. It was the second time in three games OU has had two triples.\nDeiten Lachance\nhas a hit in 10 straight games and 16 of his 17 games played, while\nBrendan Brock\nhas registered a base knock in 15 of 17 games played and is on a eight-game hit streak.\nBrock hit his team-leading fifth home run on a towering two-run shot in the sixth inning.\nJaxon Willits\nhit his second home run of the season in the sixth and 21st of his career.\nBrock and Willits hit the first back-to-back homers for the Sooners since 2024 (Anthony Mackenzie, Jackson Nicklaus vs. TCU, 5/22/24)\nThe win was OU's third victory by one run this season. OU is 3-0 in one-run games.\nUp Next\nThe Sooners and Aggies meet for the second game of the series Saturday at 4 p.m. CT before Sunday's 2 p.m. finale. All weekend is Military Appreciation Weekend at Kimrey Family Stadium. Giveaways include challenge coins for active and veteran service members.\nSeason and single game tickets for the 2026 season are available now on\nSoonerSports.com/tickets\n. For more information about Oklahoma baseball tickets, contact the OU Athletics Ticket Office at 405-325-2424, by email at\noutickets@ou.edu\nor by visiting\nSoonerSports.com/tickets\n.\nFor updates and more information on Oklahoma baseball, follow the Sooners on X and Instagram (\n@OU_Baseball\n) and like\nOklahoma Baseball\non Facebook."
